What I was referring to is curly brace placement.<p>func main() {
}<p>vs<p>func main() 
{
}<p>which produces the error &quot;prog.go:4: syntax error: unexpected semicolon or newline before {&quot;.  As I understand it this is because of the rules of where it will insert semicolons. It isn&#x27;t enforcing everything about the format which is why I said &quot;to a degree&quot; but it is still one of the most opinionated compilers on format that I know of.<p>Either way, I&#x27;m glad they did it.  The &quot;where should the curly brace go&quot; is one of the most annoying bike-sheds.
